text: Nipponaphera wallacei is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae, the nutmeg snails. The specific name wallacei is in honor of Mr. Martin Wallace, who collected type specimens. ==Description== ==Distribution== South Africa ==References== Category:Cancellariidae Category:Gastropods described in 2000
title: Nipponaphera wallacei
